div.div: Kyoukai no Kanata: I'LL BE HERE - Mirai-hen
Action, Drama, Fantasy, Romance, Slice of Life, Supernatural
This is the second part of a two-part movie. The story takes place one year after the TV series.
Shingeki no Kyojin: The Final Season

Its been four years since the Scout Regiment reached the shoreline, and the world looks different now. Things are heating up as the fate of the Scout Regimentand the people of Paradisare determined at last. However, Eren is missing. Will he reappear before age-old tensions between Marleyans and Eldians result in the war of all wars?
(Source: Crunchyroll)
Takane-san, Kimi no Koto Sukirashii yo

"I heard that Takamine-san likes you."
The head of the school discipline committee, Kengo Mashima, heard a rumor from an unknown source...... It turned out that the source was none other than Takamine-san herself, who wanted Mashima-kun to show more interest in her! But the overly serious Mashima-kun didn't get the hint: ......
"Saki Takamine, I heard you have a crush on me?"
"Why are you asking me for? ......!"
Actually, Mashima-kun liked Takamine-san, too. The first time you see these two, you'll be writhing in frustration at their innocent denseness!
(Source: Gagaga Bunko, translated)
Hokenshitsu no Otona na Senpai, Ore no Maede wa Sugu Dereru

Yuzuki, a senior member of the school infirmary committee, has a gentle and mature demeanor. Kyoji, a regular in the infirmary, got to know her as she teased him every day. He wanted to get back at her, so he said, "I like you..." When Yuzuki heard that, her behavior went haywire!?
(Source: Fantasia Bunko, translated)
